==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uphill
<hw>Up*hill"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Upwards on, or as
on, a hillside; <as>as, to walk <ex>uphill</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uphill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uphill
<hw>Up"hill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Ascending; going up; <as>as, an <ex>uphill</ex>
road</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attended with labor; difficult; <as>as,
<ex>uphill</ex> work</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uphilt</ent>⟦br⟧
